description:
When a developer adds a new mode but forgets a registration step, the feedback is silent failure or misleading output. Add runtime dev-mode checks:

```typescript
if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development') {
  const modeValues = MODE_TABS.map(t => t.value);
  const allModes: ModuleMode[] = ['neural-network', 'pipeline-builder', ...];
  for (const mode of allModes) {
    if (!modeValues.includes(mode)) {
      console.error(`[ML Design] Mode '${mode}' exists in ModuleMode but is missing from MODE_TABS array at MLDesignModule.tsx:78`);
    }
  }
}
```

This catches the most common mistake (forgot to add to MODE_TABS) with a helpful error pointing to the exact location.
